The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 30: R.S. Sharma will be the new chairman and managing director of the Oil and Natural Gas Corporation (ONGC). The public enterprise selection board today named Sharma as its first choice for the post, which has been vacant since May when Subir Raha completed his five-year term. A.K. Hazarika, the companys on-shore director, was the second choice of the selection panel, which interviewed a dozen candidates today, sources said.

 Mumbai, Aug. 30: Escorts has received approval from its board to divest its entire stake in Carraro India to joint venture partner Italy-based Carraro Spa for 20 million euros (around Rs 119 crore).

 Mumbai, Aug. 30: Nicholas Piramals group company and diagnostic laboratories chain, Wellspring, has acquired the remaining 40 per cent stake in its joint venture with Dr Phadkes Path Labs for Rs 14 crore.

 New Delhi, Aug. 30: The Telecom Disputes Settlement and Appellate Tribunal (TDSAT) will resume work with new chairman Justice Arun Kumar, a former Supreme Court judge, from next week.

 New Delhi, Aug. 30: A Norwegian court has ruled in Ranbaxys favour in the patent litigation against Pfizer for cholesterol lowering drug Atorvastatin (Lipitor).




